results.title: سوق "فوانيس مكة".. تجربة فريدة لقضاء ليالٍ رمضانية مبهجة
creator: واس - مكة المكرمة
results.description: تُثري فعاليات "فوانيس مكة" زوارها بتجربة فريدة تجمع بين الترفيه والتسوق، وتشكل نقطة جذب للراغبين في قضاء ليالٍ رمضانية مُبهجة، عبر العديد من الفعاليات الثقافية والألعاب التفاعلية والعروض الحية التي تُحاكي الموروث الشعبي وتُبرز الإبداع العصري.ويقدم سوق الفوانيس رحلة تسوق بطابع ترفيهي تُلاقي إقبالًا متزايدًا من الزوار والعائلات، خصوصًا مع اقتراب عيد الفطر.منتجات ذات جودة عاليةويوفر السوق العديد من المنتجات ذات الجودة العالية تتضمن الأزياء والإكسسوارات والعطورات، والمنتجات الغذائية، والأعمال الإبداعية، كما تتنافس الأسر المنتجة في تقديم مجموعة متنوعة من الأطعمة والمشروبات الشعبية. إضافة إلى المهن الحرفية التي تعكس التراث الثقافي السعودي، وتمثل رمزًا للفخر.وتهدف هذه الفعاليات إلى توفير تجربة ترفيهية ثقافية ثرية، لكل فئات المجتمع، ومساحة ترويجية للمشاريع المتوسطة والصغيرة، وتعزيز جودة الحياة، وتنمية وتعزيز المحتوى المحلي.

results.title: Rently Declares War on Scammers with Integrated, Data-Driven Technology for Secure and Seamless Housing Rentals
results.description: SINGAPORE, March 24, 2025 /PRNewswire/ -- Rently Pte Ltd, Singapore's fintech startup in the property sector, has declared war on rental scammers with its integrated services technologies that offer secure housing rental transactions for tenants and a smooth process for landlords. Between January and October 2024, over 430 rental scam cases were reported in Singapore, resulting in losses of at least $2.7 million. Common scam tactics include fake rental listings on Facebook and Carousell, and impersonating legitimate property agents. The surge in scams has added to market challenges, including rising vacancy rates, and increased disputes, with landlords bearing the burden of paying government wealth taxes on vacant properties. Rently addresses these challenges by offering essential solutions such as landlord verification, secure payment methods, and advanced scam prevention technologies. The platform's Rently Care service, Asia Pacific's first deposit-free subscription, provides tenants with financial flexibility while protecting them from rental scams and disputes. Rently Care allows tenants to rent without a deposit, as Rently covers the deposit for landlords, alleviating the financial burden on tenants and ensuring landlord security. A real-life example of Rently's impact is seen in the story of JM and Faz, a couple who lost S$7.2K in a deposit scam through a fake Facebook rental listing. After the incident, they turned to Rently for support and have since partnered with the platform to spread awareness about fighting rental scams, sharing their experience to help others avoid similar pitfalls. Rently enhances security by collaborating with ExpatHandovers for thorough inventory checks, often identifying hidden or costly issues that might otherwise go unnoticed. Tenants also benefit from complimentary home contents insurance underwritten by Chubb, adding an extra layer of security. All property listings on Rently are verified through Singpass MyInfo, ensuring only verified and trusted partners are listed. As an associate partner of the Real Estate Developers' Association of Singapore (REDAS), Rently collaborates with reputable co-living and serviced apartment providers, such as Habyt, Far East Hospitality, and Casa Mia, ensuring secure and reliable housing options. The platform features an AI-powered application process along with AML (Anti-Money Laundering) and anti-fraud checks, creating a safe and transparent rental environment. Rently also offers a hassle-free process for landlords. Landlords can list properties for free, receive security deposits directly from Rently, and manage contracts seamlessly with Singpass integration. Rently's platform enables landlords to draft professional-grade contracts in just 60 seconds ensuring fairness and consistency and simplifying the rental process Through Rently Pay, a free service that ensures timely rent payments, landlords receive one month of guaranteed rent payout in case of tenant default. Rently pays rent in advance to landlords and then deducts the amount from the tenant's account, ensuring the full payment is received with no deductions "At Rently, we are committed to transforming the public's perception of housing rentals by making the process secure, seamless, and scam-free. We are collaborating with Habyt to automate end-to-end payments enhances convenience and transparency. We are also planning to introduce a platform and helpline for deposit disputes, offering services and information to assist individuals in recovering their funds," said Shirley Tang, Chief Growth Officer, Rently. About Rently Founded in 2022, Rently Pte Ltd is a Singapore-based fintech startup in the property space that provides deposit-free rental solutions through their proprietary Rently Care subscription and property management services via the Rently app's inventory feature. Rently allows the flexibility of listing any property type and aims to connect potential tenants with landlords, agents, and enterprises in a secure and effective way. The platform ensures that the process of renting a property is transparent, safe, and efficient. Rently is also a subsidiary of REFIN Group Limited.

results.title: خلال 20 يومًا.. أكثر من 800 ألف مستفيد من خدمات "حافلات المدينة"
creator: واس - المدينة المنورة
results.description: أعلن مشروع "حافلات المدينة"، الذي تشرف عليه هيئة تطوير المدينة المنورة، تقديم خدمة النقل الترددي من وإلى المسجد النبوي ومسجد قباء لأكثر 850 ألف مستفيد عبر تشغيل أكثر من 35 رحلة تتنقل بزيادة تجاوزت 72% عن العام الماضي، وذلك خلال أول 20 يومًا من شهر رمضان.وبدأت حافلات المدينة نقل المصلين والزوار من أول ليلة لشهر رمضان، عبر7 مسارات من وإلى المسجد النبوي ونقطة واحدة من وإلى مسجد قباء، انطلاقًا من الاستاد الرياضي، وسيد الشهداء، وحي الخالدية، وحي شظاة، وحي الملك فهد وحي الحديقة ومواقف كلية السلام. فيما خصصت موقع مواقف السيارات في العالية مول لنقل المستفيدين إلى مسجد قباء.وتعمل جميع المسارات على مدى 18 ساعة خلال اليوم، باستثناء محطتي السلام وسيد الشهداء التي تعمل على مدى 24 ساعة.

results.title: Moscow Fashion Week Shines Light on Designers from Emerging Countries
results.description: MOSCOW, March 24, 2025 /PRNewswire/ -- In recent years, Moscow Fashion Week has solidified its position as a key platform for showcasing brands from emerging economies across the globe. Designers from Asia, Africa, and Latin America are increasingly opting for this prestigious event for their international debut. While China and India have traditionally been part of the event, each season sees a growing number of countries taking part. This spring, the runways of Moscow Fashion Week showcased diverse collections from designers coming from Indonesia, South Africa, Turkey, Tajikistan, Armenia, as well as brands from the USA and Spain. Efremov at Moscow Fashion Week The runway shows at Moscow Fashion Week consistently draw an engaged audience filling the halls. This event also plays a vital role in promoting collaborations between fashion industries and enabling designers to participate in prestigious fashion events globally. Russian designers have notably presented their collections at fashion weeks in China, India, Indonesia, and South Africa, showcasing their talent on an international stage. This spring over 200 designers converged to showcase their creations through 90 captivating shows at Moscow Fashion Week. Noteworthy among the lineup was the presence of the Chinese brand, I-La, unveiling a collection of chic ensembles tailored for the colder seasons. Hailing from Beijing, where icy winds prevail in winter, designer Li Ying artfully demonstrated that ethereal combination dresses, sheer skirts, and airy trousers with a glossy finish can effortlessly be worn even in harsh weather conditions when paired with stylish and comfortable outerwear. "Chinese-made clothing has become increasingly competitive, with its quality improving year by year. Affordable yet stylish clothing is able to meet the demands of the Russian market. As more middle and high-end clothing brands enter the Russian market, the old stereotype of Chinese goods being associated with "low price and low quality" is being challenged. The acceptance of Chinese clothing design in Russia is expected to grow steadily, indicating significant potential for further development. Fueled by the deepening Sino-Russian relations and the continuous growth of the Chinese fashion industry, the success of Chinese brands in the Russian market is highly anticipated," shared Li Ying. The Indonesian designer Reborn29 by Syukriah Rusydi captivated audiences with a stunning collection featuring fabrics by the artisans of Java. The garments such as vests and capes were adorned with a captivatingly unique torn effect, showcasing a harmonious blend of tradition and contemporary style. For international participants at Moscow Fashion Week, Russia represents a promising and expansive market brimming with potential. With unwavering confidence, they believe in the opportunity to captivate audiences with their creativity and make a resounding impact on the global stage. The Russian brand Efremov showcased a collection characterized by distinctively loose yet subtly voluminous silhouettes that perfectly balance effortless elegance and refinement. The color palettes within the collection exude a poetic elegance - combining porcelain white with gold, and chocolate brown with delicate turquoise. Meanwhile, the Moscow-based brand Persve seamlessly melds architectural precision with sensual carelessness, contrasting transparent and dense fabrics, structured and flowing forms, and matte and glossy elements. The emerging label Unke artfully evokes a game of light and shadow in its latest works, seamlessly transitioning from dark, dense fabrics to ethereal, luminescent transparencies The volume of textile products from emerging countries is on a steady upward trajectory, largely stemming from their abundant raw material reserves and deep-rooted traditions in textile production, positioning them as formidable competitors on the global stage. India, China, and Indonesia have emerged as pivotal players in the worldwide textile and apparel industry. Through their involvement in Moscow Fashion Week, brands hailing from these countries are able to showcase their offerings to a global audience, tap into potential customer bases, and garner crucial support, effectively expanding their reach and influence. About Moscow Fashion Week Moscow Fashion Week is a grand international affair showcasing 90 Fashion Shows. With a lineup of over 200 esteemed designers representing Russia, Indonesia, China, Turkey, the USA, and an array of other nations, this event is set to be a true global sensation. Moscow Fashion Week is an inspiring celebration of creativity, cultural exchange, and sartorial excellence.
